2D image of Arabidopsis inflorescence scanned in a Plustek, OpticPro A320. Set-1 image used for training.
PNG format. 
Resolution 300dpi, 3600 x 5100.

Plants were grown on an automatic watering platform within the National Plant Phenomics Centre (NPPC) (Aberystwyth University, United Kingdom) in 6cm diameter pots half filled with vermiculite and the upper half with 30% grit/sand: 70% Levington F1 (peat based compost).  The vermiculite was used to restrict plant growth.
Each plant was automatically weighed and irrigated from above to a 75% gravimetric water content daily.
Images were exported at 300 DPI and stored as 24-bit RGB images (PNG format) with image dimensions 3600 x 5100 pixels

Each plant was automatically weighed and irrigated from above to a 75% gravimetric water content daily.
Images were exported at 300 DPI and stored as 24-bit RGB images (PNG format) with image dimensions 3600 x 5100 pixels
